<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-279766E4-2950-4DFB-8398-989A2744FA99" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-279766E4-2950-4DFB-8398-989A2744FA99" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">How to save received job data</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-9C631935-A322-4774-A553-6D0B52308454"><p class="- topic/p ">In case a job is not printed as expected, you (or customers) can retrieve the job for analysis. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The print data can then be checked for compliance with the specifications. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-BD13EB05-ECF9-4C06-9D86-8AB9C82D2DE9" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Restrictions</title><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Only the last received job can be retrieved. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">This procedure can only be done on site. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-49C9705F-3469-4950-B078-E863D9957CAD" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">On site procedure</title><note id="GUID-460DC8E9-B97F-46DB-BF39-4C3FEEEF3FC2" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">This procedure requires "system administrator" rights on the printer. 
</p></note><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-D20FDCDA-1535-4FCE-9604-C156FB7FFE72" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="80*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the Settings Editor. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Browse to: Support &gt; Troubleshooting &gt; Logging and reports &gt; Store last received job: 
</p><fig id="GUID-9DB21A89-47CE-4D9A-B797-908B1B4FD105" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-DD8B9AE4-2E60-49AE-BB3E-C85EBBD545CC-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-DD8B9AE4-2E60-49AE-BB3E-C85EBBD545CC-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Locate "Store last receive job" click in the right hand column on disabled. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The System Administrator window displays: 
</p><fig id="GUID-22195F86-1D24-42CE-BAE5-0F6E46411244" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-4A83672E-8EBF-40CC-A9BA-E7A631C8A65C-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-4A83672E-8EBF-40CC-A9BA-E7A631C8A65C-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Use the correct password and log in. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The "Store of last received job" window displays: 
</p><fig id="GUID-BEB6C7C8-10C0-4129-8486-3851FFD24F2D" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-56C85EAB-1546-4D41-B592-F2FC61B76978-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-56C85EAB-1546-4D41-B592-F2FC61B76978-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check the "Enabled" radio button. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Click OK. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Submit the job with the RIP. 
</p><note id="GUID-12443737-DFB2-4ED8-8DB3-4594C40A5DCB" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">If you just want to collect the job, then you don't need to print it. You can pause the printer, submit the job with the RIP, retrieve it with the Settings Editor, delete the job on the operator panel and resume the printer again. 
</p></note></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">In the Settings Editor, browse to: Support &gt; Troubleshooting &gt; Logging and reports &gt; Download last received job. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Locate "Download last received job" click on "Download last received job" in the right hand column. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The Download last received job window displays: 
</p><fig id="GUID-F8457508-0765-4591-9C1D-042DB71235A9" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F1C12585-3CD1-4416-9C48-992E16ADFBC6-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F1C12585-3CD1-4416-9C48-992E16ADFBC6-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Click on the blueSaved_Last_Job.print to retrieve the job data. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The following message displays at the bottom of the browser window: 
</p><fig id="GUID-0AF9B8DC-A819-47F8-AB0A-5772CA7C3F5A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-38CA9B9E-6667-49D6-B2D2-0F387AE59A3D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-38CA9B9E-6667-49D6-B2D2-0F387AE59A3D-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Select ‘Save as’ and store the file at a convenient location. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">11 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">In the Settings Editor, browse to: Support &gt; Troubleshooting &gt; Logging and reports &gt; Store last received job. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Disable "Store last received job" again. 
</p><note id="GUID-E76B6732-CB9C-4CC7-B41C-ADBDA935C53B" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Do not forget this step it might slow down the printer and might cause the error 21703 (data transfer too slow). 
</p></note></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-5C937DF0-2BDD-497B-B1AC-3013A8804D24.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>